{
  "texts": [
    "Because LLMs generate predictions based on statistical patterns learned from training data, they might confidently present false information.",
    "This is particularly dangerous in critical fields such as healthcare, finance and law, where factual accuracy is essential.",
    "Models can invent statistics, references or claims, complicating the task of trustworthiness.",
    "Mitigation strategies include refining training datasets, incorporating real-time knowledge bases and enhancing human oversight during model fine-tuning.",
    "LLMs also struggle with bias amplification, as they reflect the biases present in their training data, which can perpetuate harmful stereotypes (illustrated in Figure 6, where an example of gender bias learned by the model is depicted)."
  ]
}